# Phase-4 converted-test artifacts (produced by `go2cs -tests`).
#
# The converted C# TEST SOURCES of a VALIDATED package ARE committed alongside the production
# package — `<file>_test.cs`, `package_test_info.cs`, `go2cs_test_host.cs`, and
# `<pkg>.tests.csproj` — because they are the visible, reviewable proof that the package's own
# Go test suite passes in C#. Everything the pipeline REGENERATES on each run is ignored here so
# a fresh validation from a clone leaves the tree clean:

# Go source copies staged from GOROOT for the differential `go test` baseline. This is a C#
# output tree — a `.go` file here is always a transient pipeline input, never a committed artifact.
*.go

# Run-time artifacts. The input-digest manifest embeds a machine-specific converter revision
# (the running executable's hash), and the comparison / results files are per-run output.
# NOTE: go2cs_test_disclosures.json is deliberately NOT listed here — it is the HAND-OWNED
# disclosed-divergence manifest (pinned Go=pass/C#=fail divergences the comparison oracle
# reclassifies by failure signature), authored and committed like source, never regenerated.
go2cs_test_manifest.json
go2cs_test_comparison.json
go2cs_test_results.json
go2cs_test_results.xml
